mtrapinfoBmEventId.name: mtrapinfoBmEventId
mtrapinfoBmEventId.description: Allow CPS traps with an integer argument for providing detail information about Battery Manager specific event identifier. Not being defined in the MIB, only reply 0. Known Specific Event ID: Battery Manager 0 - not used 1 - Alarm: The battery manager system fault. 2 - Info: Device configuration changed. 3 - Alarm: Probe configuration mismatched. 4 - Info: Probe configuration matched. 5 - Alarm: Communication with battery manager has been lost. 6 - Info: Communication with battery manager has been restored. 7 - Alarm: Communication with LCD has been lost. 8 - Info: Communication with LCD has been restored. 9 - Warning: Enter battery equalization active mode. 10- Warning: Leave battery equalization active mode. 11- Alarm: Battery equalizing has failed. 12- Info: Battery equalizing succeed. Known Specific Event ID: Battery Probes 101 - Alarm: Low battery voltage. 102 - Alarm: High battery voltage. 103 - Info: Battery voltage event has cleared. 104 - Alarm: Low battery temperature. 105 - Alarm: High battery temperature. 106 - Info: Battery temperature event has cleared. 107 - Alarm: Critical low battery resistance. 108 - Alarm: Critical high battery resistance. 109 - Warning: Low battery resistance. 110 - Warning: high battery resistance. 111 - Info: Battery resistance event has cleared. 112 - Alarm: Battery resistance health has crossed alarm threshold. 113 - Warning: Battery resistance health has crossed warning threshold. 114 - Info: Battery resistance health has returned to Normal.

upsAdvanceConfigRatedOutputVoltage.name: upsAdvanceConfigRatedOutputVoltage
upsAdvanceConfigRatedOutputVoltage.description: The standard UPS output voltage in VAC. The possible values are 100, 110, 120, 127, 208, 220, 230, and 240. If a value other than a possible value is set, it will not be accepted.

upsAdvanceConfigHighTransferVolt.name: upsAdvanceConfigHighTransferVolt
upsAdvanceConfigHighTransferVolt.description: Adjust the high transfer vloltage in VAC. The high transfer vloltage will become the UPS default value subtracts this value. The allowed values depend on the output: 100-127 volt system allow settings of 0-15. 208-240 volt system allow settings of 0-30. If the adjustable value is over the allowed values, it will not be accepted.

upsAdvanceConfigLowTransferVolt.name: upsAdvanceConfigLowTransferVolt
upsAdvanceConfigLowTransferVolt.description: Adjust the low transfer vloltage in VAC. The low transfer vloltage will become the UPS default value adds this value. The allowed values depend on the output: 100-127 volt system allow settings of 0-15. 208-240 volt system allow settings of 0-30. If the adjustable value is over the allowed values, it will not be accepted.

upsAdvanceConfigAlarm.name: upsAdvanceConfigAlarm
upsAdvanceConfigAlarm.description: This value is set to handle audible alarms when power failure.

upsAdvanceConfigAlarmTimer.name: upsAdvanceConfigAlarmTimer
upsAdvanceConfigAlarmTimer.description: The time after power failure at which the UPS begins giving audible alarms. This timer is effective only if the value of upsAdvanceConfigAlarm is timed(1). Accepted values are between 0 to 60 seconds. If a value other than a supported value is set, the value will not be accepted.

upsAdvanceConfigMinReturnCapacity.name: upsAdvanceConfigMinReturnCapacity
upsAdvanceConfigMinReturnCapacity.description: The minimum battery capacity that UPS will return from a low battery shutdown condition. The possible values are between 0 to 40. If a value other than a supported value is set, the value will not be accepted.

upsAdvanceConfigSensitivity.name: upsAdvanceConfigSensitivity
upsAdvanceConfigSensitivity.description: The sensitivity of the UPS to power failure detection.

upsAdvanceConfigLowBatteryRunTime.name: upsAdvanceConfigLowBatteryRunTime
upsAdvanceConfigLowBatteryRunTime.description: The desired run time, in seconds, UPS will enter in a low battery sequence. The possible values are 120, 300, 420, 600. If a value other than a supported value is set, the value will not be accepted.

upsAdvanceConfigReturnDelay.name: upsAdvanceConfigReturnDelay
upsAdvanceConfigReturnDelay.description: The delay time the UPS will turn on after power recovery. The value is also used in a 'reboot' or 'wake up' sequence. The possible values are 0 to 600 seconds. If a value other than a supported value is set, the value will not be accepted.

upsAdvanceConfigShutoffDelay.name: upsAdvanceConfigShutoffDelay
upsAdvanceConfigShutoffDelay.description: The delay time the UPS will remain on after receiving a turn off command. The possible values are between 1 to 99 minutes. If a value other than a supported value is set, the value will not be accepted.

upsAdvanceConfigSleepDelay.name: upsAdvanceConfigSleepDelay
upsAdvanceConfigSleepDelay.description: The delay time the UPS will enter sleep mode after receiving a sleep command. WThe possible values are between 1 to 99 minutes. If a value other than a supported value is set, the value will not be accepted.

upsAdvanceConfigSetEEPROMDefaults.name: upsAdvanceConfigSetEEPROMDefaults
upsAdvanceConfigSetEEPROMDefaults.description: Reset the UPS EEPROM parameters to default values.

upsAdvanceConfigAutoRestore.name: upsAdvanceConfigAutoRestore
upsAdvanceConfigAutoRestore.description: When this option is enabled, the UPS will restore output immediately when the utility power restores.When this option is disabled, the UPS will not restore output at that moment and users have to turn it on manually at a later time.

upsAdvanceConfigRechargedCapacity.name: upsAdvanceConfigRechargedCapacity
upsAdvanceConfigRechargedCapacity.description: When the utility power restores, the UPS will start to recharge until the specified battery capacity in percentage is met before restoring output power. The possible values are 0, 15, 30, 45, 60, 75, and 90. If a value other than a possible value is set, it will not be accepted.

upsAdvanceConfigColdStart.name: upsAdvanceConfigColdStart
upsAdvanceConfigColdStart.description: Set the ability of the UPS can start in the absence of input power.When this option is enabled the UPS can be turned on without having input power.

upsAdvanceConfigDeepDischargeProtection.name: upsAdvanceConfigDeepDischargeProtection
upsAdvanceConfigDeepDischargeProtection.description: When the UPS is on Battery Mode with 0% load and the status remains for the time configured,the RMCARD will enforce the UPS to Sleep Mode and the output will be turned off. The possible values are 0, 20, 40, and 60 minutes. If a value other than a possible value is set, it will not be accepted.

upsAdvanceConfigSleepAfterAllClientShut.name: upsAdvanceConfigSleepAfterAllClientShut
upsAdvanceConfigSleepAfterAllClientShut.description: If this option is enabled, UPS will enter sleep mode after utility power failed and remaining MSDT+2 minutes.More information about MSDT please reference to help page of UPS - > PowerPanel List.

upsBaseControlConserveBattery.name: upsBaseControlConserveBattery
upsBaseControlConserveBattery.description: UPS on battery will enter sleeping when the variable is set to turnOffUpsToConserveBattery(2). When utility power recovers the UPS will turn back on. Trying to turn off a UPS that is not on battery mode will cause badValue error. It is no effective to set this value to noTurnOffUps(1).

upsAdvanceControlUpsOff.name: upsAdvanceControlUpsOff
upsAdvanceControlUpsOff.description: UPS will shutdown when the variable is set to turnUpsOff(2). UPS will shutdown after a delay period specified by upsAdvanceConfigShutoffDelay when the variable is Set to turnUpsOffGracefully(3). Without regard to the utility state the UPS will not provide output power in this state. It is no effective to set this value to noTurnUpsOff(1).

upsAdvanceControlRebootUps.name: upsAdvanceControlRebootUps
upsAdvanceControlRebootUps.description: UPS will shutdown and turn back on when the variable is set to rebootUps(2). It is no effective to set this value to noRebootUps(1).

upsAdvanceControlUpsSleep.name: upsAdvanceControlUpsSleep
upsAdvanceControlUpsSleep.description: UPS will enter sleep mode when the variable is set to putUpsToSleep(2). UPS will enter sleep mode after a delay period specified by upsAdvanceConfigSleepDelay when the variable is Set to putUpsToSleepGracefully(3). Without regard to the utility state the UPS will not provide output power in sleep mode. Output power will recover when specified time has elapsed. It is no effective to set this value to noPutUpsToSleep(1).

upsAdvanceControlSimulatePowerFail.name: upsAdvanceControlSimulatePowerFail
upsAdvanceControlSimulatePowerFail.description: UPS will transfer to backup mode when the variable is set to simulatePowerFailure(2). It is no effective to set this value to noFlashAndBeep(1).

upsAdvanceControlFlashAndBeep.name: upsAdvanceControlFlashAndBeep
upsAdvanceControlFlashAndBeep.description: UPS will beep and simultaneously turn on the panel lights when the variable is set to flashAndBeep(2). It is no effective to set this value to noSimulatePowerFailure(1).

upsAdvanceControlTurnOnUPS.name: upsAdvanceControlTurnOnUPS
upsAdvanceControlTurnOnUPS.description: UPS will turned on immediately when the variable is set to turnOnUPS(2). It is no effective to set this value to noTurnOnUPS(1).

upsAdvanceTestDiagnosticSchedule.name: upsAdvanceTestDiagnosticSchedule
upsAdvanceTestDiagnosticSchedule.description: The schedule of the UPS automatic selftest.

upsAdvanceTestDiagnostics.name: upsAdvanceTestDiagnostics
upsAdvanceTestDiagnostics.description: UPS will do a diagnostic selftest when the variable is set to testDiagnostics(2). It is no effective to set this value to noTestDiagnostics(1).

upsAdvanceTestLastDiagnosticsDate.name: upsAdvanceTestLastDiagnosticsDate
upsAdvanceTestLastDiagnosticsDate.description: The last UPS selftest date in mm/dd/yy format.

upsAdvanceTestIndicators.name: upsAdvanceTestIndicators
upsAdvanceTestIndicators.description: UPS will perform a panel indicator test when the variable is set to testIndicators(2). It is no effective to set this value to noTestIndicators(1).

upsAdvanceTestRuntimeCalibration.name: upsAdvanceTestRuntimeCalibration
upsAdvanceTestRuntimeCalibration.description: UPS will discharge to calibrate the UPS runtime when the variable is set to performCalibration(2). This test runs until the UPS is in a low battery condition. UPS will cancel the discharge after setting performCalibration(2) when the variable is set to cancelCurrentCalibration(3). It is no effective to set this value to noPerformCalibration(1). The result of the runtime test will be stored in upsAdvanceTestCalibrationResults.

upsAdvanceTestCalibrationResults.name: upsAdvanceTestCalibrationResults
upsAdvanceTestCalibrationResults.description: The last runtime calibration result. This value means : - ok(1), if a successful runtime calibration. - invalidCalibration(2), if runtime calibration failure. - calibrationInProgress(3), if calibration is processing now.

upsAdvanceTestCalibrationDate.name: upsAdvanceTestCalibrationDate
upsAdvanceTestCalibrationDate.description: The last UPS runtime calibration date

If the outlet bank is off, the immediateOff (2) value will be returned. If the outlet bank is critical (uncontrollable), the criticalBank (4) value will be returned. Setting this variable to immediateOn (1) will immediately turn the outlet on. Setting this variable to immediateOff (2) will immediately turn the outlet off.

The index from left to right is outlet#8, #7, #6, #5, #4, #3, #2, #1. ePDUIdentName.description: The name of the Rack PDU. The maximum string size is device dependent.

ePDUIdentHardwareRev.name: ePDUIdentHardwareRev
ePDUIdentHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision of the Rack PDU. This value is set at the factory.

ePDUIdentFirmwareRev.name: ePDUIdentFirmwareRev
ePDUIdentFirmwareRev.description: An 8-byte ID string identifying the Rack PDU firmware revision. This value is set at the factory.

ePDUIdentDateOfManufacture.name: ePDUIdentDateOfManufacture
ePDUIdentDateOfManufacture.description: The date when the Rack PDU was manufactured in mm/dd/yyyy format. This value is set at the factory. The year 2000 will be represented by 00.

ePDUIdentModelNumber.name: ePDUIdentModelNumber
ePDUIdentModelNumber.description: A 10-character string identifying the model number of the Rack PDU. This value is set at the factory.

ePDUIdentSerialNumber.name: ePDUIdentSerialNumber
ePDUIdentSerialNumber.description: A 12-character string identifying the serial number of the Rack PDU. This value is set at the factory.

ePDUIdentDeviceRating.name: ePDUIdentDeviceRating
ePDUIdentDeviceRating.description: Getting this OID will return the electrical rating of the device.

ePDUIdentDeviceNumOutlets.name: ePDUIdentDeviceNumOutlets
ePDUIdentDeviceNumOutlets.description: Getting this OID will return the number of outlets contained in the device.

ePDUIdentDeviceNumPhases.name: ePDUIdentDeviceNumPhases
ePDUIdentDeviceNumPhases.description: Getting this OID will return the number of phases supported by the device.

ePDUIdentDeviceNumBreakers.name: ePDUIdentDeviceNumBreakers
ePDUIdentDeviceNumBreakers.description: Getting this OID will return the number of circuit breakers supported by the device. This is the same as the number of banks of outlets. 0 will be returned if the unit has no phase breakers.

ePDUIdentDeviceBreakerRating.name: ePDUIdentDeviceBreakerRating
ePDUIdentDeviceBreakerRating.description: Getting this OID will return rating of the circuit breakers on the device if it has any.

ePDUIdentDeviceOrientation.name: ePDUIdentDeviceOrientation
ePDUIdentDeviceOrientation.description: Getting this OID will return the intended physical orientation of the device. OrientHorizonatal(1) indicates Horizontal. OrientVertical(2) indicates Vertical.

ePDUIdentDeviceOutletLayout.name: ePDUIdentDeviceOutletLayout
ePDUIdentDeviceOutletLayout.description: Getting this OID will return outlet layout for the device. SeqPhaseToNeutral(1) indicates outlet layout as follows: 1:1-N,2:2-N,3:3-N,4:1-N,5:2-N,... SeqPhaseToPhase(2) indicates outlet layout as follows: 1:1-2,2:2-3,3:3-1,4:1-2,5:2-3,... SeqPhToNeu21PhToPh(3) indicates outlet layout as follows: 1:1-N,2:2-N...21:3-N,22:1-2,23:2-3,24:3-1,... SeqPhToPhGrouped(4) indicates outlet layout as follows: Otlts1-8::(3-1),Otlts9-16::(2-3),Otlts17-24::(1-2).

ePDUIdentDeviceDisplayOrientation.name: ePDUIdentDeviceDisplayOrientation
ePDUIdentDeviceDisplayOrientation.description: Getting this OID will return the intended physical orientation of the Seven-Segment Display. displayNormal(1) indicates Normal. displayReverse(2)indicates Upside-Down. displayRotate90(3) indicates rotate 90 degree. displayRotate270(4) indicates rotate 270 degree. displayAuto(5) indicates auto-detect and rotate.

ePDUIdentDeviceLinetoLineVoltage.name: ePDUIdentDeviceLinetoLineVoltage
ePDUIdentDeviceLinetoLineVoltage.description: Getting/Setting this OID will return/set the Line to Line Volatage. The valid range is between 0V to 440V

ePDUIdentIndicator.name: ePDUIdentIndicator
ePDUIdentIndicator.description: PDU will perform a panel indicator test when the variable is set to testIndicators(2). It is no effective to set this value to noTestIndicators(1).

ePDULoadDevMaxPhaseLoad.name: ePDULoadDevMaxPhaseLoad
ePDULoadDevMaxPhaseLoad.description: Getting this OID will return the maximum rated power that each phase of the Rack PDU can provide. It is represented in Amps. 0 will be returned if the unit is banked.

ePDULoadDevNumPhases.name: ePDULoadDevNumPhases
ePDULoadDevNumPhases.description: The number of phases available with this Rack PDU.

ePDULoadDevMaxBankLoad.name: ePDULoadDevMaxBankLoad
ePDULoadDevMaxBankLoad.description: Getting this OID will return the maximum rated power that a bank of the Rack PDU can provide. It is represented in Amps. 0 will be returned if the device does not have any banks.

ePDULoadDevNumBanks.name: ePDULoadDevNumBanks
ePDULoadDevNumBanks.description: The number of banks of outlets available with this Rack PDU. A bank of outlets has a unique circuit breaker for a subset of the total number of outlets on the ePDU. 0 will be returned if the unit no banks.

ePDULoadDevBankMaxLoad.name: ePDULoadDevBankMaxLoad
ePDULoadDevBankMaxLoad.description: Getting this OID will return the maximum rated power that each bank of the Rack PDU can provide. It is represented in Amps.

ePDULoadPhaseConfigTable.name: ePDULoadPhaseConfigTable
ePDULoadPhaseConfigTable.description: Allows for configuration of each Rack PDU phase. The number of entries is contained in the ePDULoadDevNumPhases OID.

ePDULoadPhaseConfigEntry.name: ePDULoadPhaseConfigEntry
ePDULoadPhaseConfigEntry.description: The Rack PDU phase to configure.

ePDULoadPhaseConfigIndex.name: ePDULoadPhaseConfigIndex
ePDULoadPhaseConfigIndex.description: The index to the Rack PDU phase entry.

ePDULoadPhaseConfigLowLoadThreshold.name: ePDULoadPhaseConfigLowLoadThreshold
ePDULoadPhaseConfigLowLoadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load is nearing a low consumption condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is less than the threshold value. A threshold value of 0 Amps effectively disables this warning. Maximum value must be less than the value returned by the ePDULoadPhaseConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID.

ePDULoadPhaseConfigNearOverloadThreshold.name: ePDULoadPhaseConfigNearOverloadThreshold
ePDULoadPhaseConfigNearOverloadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load is nearing an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value. Minimum value must be greater than the value returned by the ePDULoadPhaseConfigLowLoadThreshold OID. Maximum value must be less than or equal to the value returned by the ePDULoadPhaseConfigOverloadThreshold OID.

ePDULoadPhaseConfigOverloadThreshold.name: ePDULoadPhaseConfigOverloadThreshold
ePDULoadPhaseConfigOverloadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load has entered an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value. Minimum value must be greater than or equal to the value returned by the ePDULoadPhaseConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID. Maximum value must be less than or equal to the value returned by the ePDULoadDevMaxPhaseLoad OID.

ePDULoadPhaseConfigAlarm.name: ePDULoadPhaseConfigAlarm
ePDULoadPhaseConfigAlarm.description: Getting this OID will return the current Phase Alarm.

ePDULoadStatusTable.name: ePDULoadStatusTable
ePDULoadStatusTable.description: Allows for getting of status of each Rack PDU phase/bank. The number of entries is calculated by adding the number of phases (ePDULoadDevNumPhases OID) and the number of banks of outlets (ePDULoadDevNumBanks) Number of entries = #phases + #banks. NOTE: If a device has phase and bank information, all phase information shall precede the bank information.

ePDULoadStatusEntry.name: ePDULoadStatusEntry
ePDULoadStatusEntry.description: The Rack PDU phase/bank to gather status from.

ePDULoadStatusIndex.name: ePDULoadStatusIndex
ePDULoadStatusIndex.description: The index to the Rack PDU phase/bank entry. All phase information will precede any bank information

ePDULoadStatusLoad.name: ePDULoadStatusLoad
ePDULoadStatusLoad.description: Getting this OID will return the phase/bank load measured in tenths of Amps.

ePDULoadStatusLoadState.name: ePDULoadStatusLoadState
ePDULoadStatusLoadState.description: Getting this OID will return the phase/bank load state. loadNormal(1) indicates that the phase/bank is operating properly within the ePDULoadConfigLowLoadThreshold and ePDULoadConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID values. loadLow(2) indicates that the phase/bank load has dropped below the ePDULoadConfigLowLoadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. loadNearOverload(3) indicates that the phase/bank load is greater than or equal to the ePDULoadConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared. loadOverload(4) indicates that the phase/bank load is greater than or equal to the ePDULoadConfigOverloadThreshold OID value. An SNMP trap will occur when this state is entered or cleared.

ePDULoadStatusPhaseNumber.name: ePDULoadStatusPhaseNumber
ePDULoadStatusPhaseNumber.description: The phase number to which this record refers.

ePDULoadStatusBankNumber.name: ePDULoadStatusBankNumber
ePDULoadStatusBankNumber.description: The bank number to which this record refers. A value of 0 will be returned if any bank is not present or if it is phase related.

ePDULoadStatusVoltage.name: ePDULoadStatusVoltage
ePDULoadStatusVoltage.description: Getting this OID will return the phase/bank voltage measured in 0.1 volts.

ePDULoadStatusActivePower.name: ePDULoadStatusActivePower

ePDULoadStatusApparentPower.name: ePDULoadStatusApparentPower
ePDULoadStatusApparentPower.description: Getting this OID will return the phase/bank apparent power measured in VA.

ePDULoadStatusPowerFactor.name: ePDULoadStatusPowerFactor
ePDULoadStatusPowerFactor.description: Getting this OID will return power factor of the output measured in hundredths. A value of 100 representing a unity power factor (1.00).

ePDULoadStatusEnergy.name: ePDULoadStatusEnergy
ePDULoadStatusEnergy.description: Getting this OID will return the phase/bank apparent power measured in 0.1 kilowatt-hours.

ePDULoadStatusEnergyStartTime.name: ePDULoadStatusEnergyStartTime
ePDULoadStatusEnergyStartTime.description: Getting this OID will return the date and time of the last energy meter reset

ePDULoadBankConfigTable.name: ePDULoadBankConfigTable
ePDULoadBankConfigTable.description: Allows for configuration of each Rack PDU bank. The number of entries is contained in the ePDULoadDevNumBanks OID.

ePDULoadBankConfigEntry.name: ePDULoadBankConfigEntry
ePDULoadBankConfigEntry.description: The Rack PDU bank to configure.

ePDULoadBankConfigIndex.name: ePDULoadBankConfigIndex
ePDULoadBankConfigIndex.description: The index to the Rack PDU bank entry.

ePDULoadBankConfigLowLoadThreshold.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load is nearing a low consumption condition. It is represented in Amps. ePDULoadBankConfigNearOverloadThreshold.name: ePDULoadBankConfigNearOverloadThreshold

Maximum value must be less than or equal to the value returned by the ePDULoadDevMaxBankLoad OID.

ePDULoadBankConfigAlarm.name: ePDULoadBankConfigAlarm
ePDULoadBankConfigAlarm.description: Getting this OID will return the current Bank Alarm.

ePDUOutletDevCommand.name: ePDUOutletDevCommand
ePDUOutletDevCommand.description: Setting this OID to immediateAllOn (2) will turn all outlets on immediately. Setting this OID to immediateAllOff (3) will turn all outlets off immediately. Setting this OID to immediateAllReboot (4) will reboot all outlets immediately. Setting this OID to delayedAllOn (5) will turn all outlets on as defined by each outlet's ePDUOutletConfigPowerOnTime OID value. Setting this OID to delayedAllOff (6) will turn all outlets off as defined by each outlet's ePDUOutletConfigPowerOffTime OID value. Setting this OID to delayedAllReboot (7) will cause a delayedAllOff command to be performed. Once all outlets are off, the Switched Rack PDU will then delay the largest ePDUOutletConfigRebootDuration OID time, and then perform a delayedAllOn command. Setting this OID to cancelAllPendingCommands (8) will cause all pending commands on the Switched Rack PDU to be canceled. Getting this OID will return the noCommandAll (1) value.

ePDUOutletDevColdstartDelay.name: ePDUOutletDevColdstartDelay
ePDUOutletDevColdstartDelay.description: The amount of delay, in seconds, between when power is provided to the Switched Rack PDU and when the Switched Rack PDU provides basic master power to the outlets. Allowed values are: -1 - never apply power automatically. 0 - apply power immediately. 1 to 300 - delay up to 300 seconds (5 minutes).

ePDUOutletDevNumCntrlOutlets.name: ePDUOutletDevNumCntrlOutlets
ePDUOutletDevNumCntrlOutlets.description: The number of controlled outlets on this Switched Rack PDU.

ePDUOutletDevNumTotalOutlets.name: ePDUOutletDevNumTotalOutlets
ePDUOutletDevNumTotalOutlets.description: The total number of outlets on this Rack PDU.

ePDUOutletDevMonitoredOutlets.name: ePDUOutletDevMonitoredOutlets
ePDUOutletDevMonitoredOutlets.description: The total number of monitored outlets on this Rack PDU.

ePDUOutletDevColdstartState.name: ePDUOutletDevColdstartState
ePDUOutletDevColdstartState.description: The ePDU outlet state after coldstart. Allowed values are: 1 - all outlets on after coldstart. 2 - outlet status same as previous state.

ePDUOutletPhaseTable.name: ePDUOutletPhaseTable
ePDUOutletPhaseTable.description: Allows for management of outlets on a per phase basis.

ePDUOutletPhaseIndex.name: ePDUOutletPhaseIndex
ePDUOutletPhaseIndex.description: The index to the Switched Rack PDU phase entry.

ePDUOutletPhaseOverloadRestriction.name: ePDUOutletPhaseOverloadRestriction
ePDUOutletPhaseOverloadRestriction.description: This OID controls the behavior of a Switched Rack PDU phase when an overload condition is possible and additional outlets are requested to be turned on. Setting this OID to alwaysAllowTurnON (1) will always allow the outlets on the corresponding phase to turn on. Setting this OID to restrictOnNearOverload (2) will not allow outlets on the corresponding phase to turn on if the ePDULoadConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID is exceeded. Setting this OID to restrictOnOverload (3) will not allow outlets on the corresponding phase to turn on if the ePDULoadConfigOverloadThreshold OID is exceeded.

ePDUOutletControlTable.name: ePDUOutletControlTable
ePDUOutletControlTable.description: Allows for control of the individual outlets. The number of entries is contained in the ePDUOutletDevNumCntrlOutlets OID.

ePDUOutletControlIndex.name: ePDUOutletControlIndex
ePDUOutletControlIndex.description: The index to the outlet entry.

ePDUOutletControlOutletName.name: ePDUOutletControlOutletName
ePDUOutletControlOutletName.description: The name of the outlet. The maximum string size is device dependent. An error will be returned if the set request exceeds the max size. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

ePDUOutletControlOutletPhase.name: ePDUOutletControlOutletPhase
ePDUOutletControlOutletPhase.description: The phase/s associated with this outlet. For single phase devices, this object will always return phase1(1). For 3-phase devices, this object will return phase1 (1), phase2 (2), or phase3 (3) for outlets tied to a single phase. For outlets tied to two phases, this object will return phase1-2 (4) for phases 1 and 2, phase2-3 (5) for phases 2 and 3, and phase3-1 (6) for phases 3 and 1.

ePDUOutletControlOutletCommand.name: ePDUOutletControlOutletCommand
ePDUOutletControlOutletCommand.description: Getting this variable will return the outlet state. If the outlet is on, the immediateOn (1) value will be returned. If the outlet is off, the immediateOff (2) value will be returned. Setting this variable to immediateOn (1) will immediately turn the outlet on. Setting this variable to immediateOff (2) will immediately turn the outlet off. Setting this variable to immediateReboot (3) will immediately reboot the outlet. Setting this variable to delayedOn (4) will turn the outlet on after the ePDUOutletConfigPowerOnTime OID time has elapsed. Setting this variable to delayedOff (5) will turn the outlet off after the ePDUOutletConfigPowerOffTime OID time has elapsed. Setting this variable to delayedReboot (6) will cause the Switched Rack PDU to perform a delayedOff command, wait the ePDUOutletConfigRebootDuration OID time, and then perform a delayedOn command. Setting this variable to cancelPendingCommand (7) will cause any pending command to this outlet to be canceled. Setting this variable to outletIdentify (8) will cause PDU LED to display the number of the outlet.

ePDUOutletControlOutletBank.name: ePDUOutletControlOutletBank
ePDUOutletControlOutletBank.description: The bank associated with this outlet.

ePDUOutletConfigTable.name: ePDUOutletConfigTable
ePDUOutletConfigTable.description: Allows for configuration of individual outlets. The number of entries is contained in the ePDUOutletDevNumCntrlOutlets OID.

ePDUOutletConfigIndex.name: ePDUOutletConfigIndex
ePDUOutletConfigIndex.description: The index to the outlet entry.

ePDUOutletConfigOutletName.name: ePDUOutletConfigOutletName
ePDUOutletConfigOutletName.description: The name of the outlet. The maximum string size is device dependent. An error will be returned if the set request exceeds the max size.

ePDUOutletConfigOutletPhase.name: ePDUOutletConfigOutletPhase
ePDUOutletConfigOutletPhase.description: The phase/s associated with this outlet. For single phase devices, this object will always return phase1(1). For 3-phase devices, this object will return phase1 (1), phase2 (2), or phase3 (3) for outlets tied to a single phase. For outlets tied to two phases, this object will return phase1-2 (4) for phases 1 and 2, phase2-3 (5) for phases 2 and 3, and phase3-1 (6) for phases 3 and 1.

ePDUOutletConfigPowerOnTime.name: ePDUOutletConfigPowerOnTime
ePDUOutletConfigPowerOnTime.description: The amount of time (in seconds) the outlet will delay powering on at coldstart or when a command that requires a turn-on delay is issued. Allowed values are: -1 - never power on. 0 - power on immediately. 1 to 7200 - power on up to 7200 seconds after being commanded.

ePDUOutletConfigPowerOffTime.name: ePDUOutletConfigPowerOffTime
ePDUOutletConfigPowerOffTime.description: The amount of time (in seconds) the outlet will delay powering off when a command that requires a turn-off delay is issued. Allowed values are: -1 - never power off. 0 - power off immediately. 1 to 7200 - power off up to 7200 seconds after being commanded.

ePDUOutletConfigRebootDuration.name: ePDUOutletConfigRebootDuration
ePDUOutletConfigRebootDuration.description: During a reboot sequence, power is turned off and then back on. This OID defines the amount of time to wait, in seconds, after turning the power off, at the start of the sequence, before turning power back on, at the end of the reboot sequence. Allowed range is any value between 5 and 60 seconds (1 minute).

ePDUOutletConfigOutletBank.name: ePDUOutletConfigOutletBank
ePDUOutletConfigOutletBank.description: The bank associated with this outlet.

ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredTableSize.name: ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredTableSize
ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredTableSize.description: The size of the Outlet Config Monitored Table

ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredEntry.name: ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredEntry
ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredEntry.description: This gives access to Monitored Outlet entries

ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredIndex.name: ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredIndex

ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredName.description: The name of the Monitored Outlet. The maximum string size is device dependent. An error will be returned if the set request exceeds the max size.

ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredNumber.name: ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredNumber
ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredNumber.description: The outlet number of an Outlet Monitored RACK PDU.

ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredLowLoadThreshol.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load is nearing a low consumption condition. It is represented in watts. A warning will be issued when the load is less than the threshold value. A threshold value of 0 effectively disables this warning. Maximum value must be less than the value returned by the ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredNearOverloadThreshold OID. 0 will be returned if the unit is not Outlet Monitored Rack PDU.

ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredNearOverloadThr.name: ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredNearOverloadThreshold
ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredNearOverloadThr.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load is nearing an overload condition. It is represented in watts. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value. Minimum value must be greater than the value returned by the ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredLowLoadThreshold OID. ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredOverloadThresho.name: ePDUOutletConfigMonitoredOverloadThreshold

atsLoadCfgBankLowLoad.name: atsLoadCfgBankLowLoad
atsLoadCfgBankLowLoad.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load is nearing a low consumption condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is less than the threshold value. A threshold value of 0 Amps effectively disables this warning.

atsLoadCfgBankNearOverLoad.name: atsLoadCfgBankNearOverLoad
atsLoadCfgBankNearOverLoad.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load is nearing an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value.

atsLoadCfgBankOverLoad.name: atsLoadCfgBankOverLoad
atsLoadCfgBankOverLoad.description: A threshold that indicates the power consumption of the load has entered an overload condition. It is represented in Amps. A warning will be issued when the load is greater than or equal to the threshold value.

atsLoadCfgBankOutletRestriction.name: atsLoadCfgBankOutletRestriction
atsLoadCfgBankOutletRestriction.description: This OID controls the behavior of a ATS phase when an overload condition is possible and additional outlets are requested to be turned on. Setting this OID to alwaysAllowTurnON (1) will always allow the outlets on the corresponding phase to turn on. Setting this OID to restrictOnNearOverload (2) will not allow outlets on the corresponding phase to turn on if the ePDULoadConfigNearOverloadThreshold OID is exceeded. Setting this OID to restrictOnOverload (3) will not allow outlets on the corresponding phase to turn on if the ePDULoadConfigOverloadThreshold OID is exceeded.

atsOutletDevTotalOutletNum.name: atsOutletDevTotalOutletNum
atsOutletDevTotalOutletNum.description: The total number of outlets on the ATS.

atsOutletDevCtrlOutletNum.name: atsOutletDevCtrlOutletNum
atsOutletDevCtrlOutletNum.description: The number of controlled outlets on the ATS.

atsOutletDevColdStartDelay.name: atsOutletDevColdStartDelay
atsOutletDevColdStartDelay.description: The amount of delay, in seconds, between when power is provided to the ATS and when the ATS provides basic master power to the outlets. Allowed values are: -1 - never apply power automatically. 0 - apply power immediately. 1 to 300 - delay up to 300 seconds (5 minutes).

atsOutletDevColdStartState.name: atsOutletDevColdStartState
atsOutletDevColdStartState.description: The ATS outlet state after coldstart. Allowed values are: 1 - all outlets on after coldstart. 2 - outlet status same as previous state.

atsOutletDevLocalCtrl.name: atsOutletDevLocalCtrl
atsOutletDevLocalCtrl.description: To configure enable or disable outlet local control function.

atsOutletDevCommand.name: atsOutletDevCommand
atsOutletDevCommand.description: Setting this OID to immediateAllOn (2) will turn all outlets on immediately. Setting this OID to immediateAllOff (3) will turn all outlets off immediately. Setting this OID to immediateAllReboot (4) will reboot all outlets immediately. Setting this OID to delayedAllOn (5) will turn all outlets on as defined by each outlet's atsOutletCfgPowerOnTime OID value. Setting this OID to delayedAllOff (6) will turn all outlets off as defined by each outlet's atsOutletCfgPowerOffTime OID value. Setting this OID to delayedAllReboot (7) will cause a delayedAllOff command to be performed. Once all outlets are off, the Switched Rack ATS will then delay the largest atsOutletCfgRebootDuration OID time, and then perform a delayedAllOn command. Setting this OID to cancelAllPendingCommands (8) will cause all pending commands on the Switched Rack ATS to be canceled. Getting this OID will return the noCommandAll (1) value.

atsOutletStatusTableSize.name: atsOutletStatusTableSize
atsOutletStatusTableSize.description: The size of the outlet status table.

atsOutletStatusTable.description: Allows for getting of status of individual outlets.

atsOutletStatusEntry.name: atsOutletStatusEntry
atsOutletStatusEntry.description: The outlet to gather status from.

atsOutletStatusTableIndex.name: atsOutletStatusTableIndex
atsOutletStatusTableIndex.description: The index to the outlet entry.

atsOutletStatusOutletName.name: atsOutletStatusOutletName
atsOutletStatusOutletName.description: The name of the outlet. The maximum string size is device dependent. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

atsOutletStatusOutletState.name: atsOutletStatusOutletState
atsOutletStatusOutletState.description: Getting this variable will return the outlet state. If the outlet is on, the outletStatusOn (1) value will be returned. If the outlet is off, the outletStatusOff (2) value will be returned.

atsOutletStatusOutletCmdPending.name: atsOutletStatusOutletCmdPending
atsOutletStatusOutletCmdPending.description: Getting this variable will return the command pending state of the outlet. If a command is pending on the outlet, the outletStatusCommandPending (1) value will be returned. If there is not a command pending on the outlet, the outletStatusNoCommandPending (2) will be returned.

atsOutletStatusOutletPhase.name: atsOutletStatusOutletPhase
atsOutletStatusOutletPhase.description: The phase/s associated with this outlet. For single phase devices, this object will always return phase1(1). For 3-phase devices, this object will return phase1 (1), phase2 (2), or phase3 (3) for outlets tied to a single phase. For outlets tied to two phases, this object will return phase1-2 (4) for phases 1 and 2, phase2-3 (5) for phases 2 and 3, and phase3-1 (6) for phases 3 and 1.

atsOutletStatusOutletBank.name: atsOutletStatusOutletBank
atsOutletStatusOutletBank.description: The bank associated with this outlet.

atsOutletCtrlTableSize.name: atsOutletCtrlTableSize
atsOutletCtrlTableSize.description: The size of the outlet control table.

atsOutletCtrlTable.name: atsOutletCtrlTable
atsOutletCtrlTable.description: Allows for control of the individual outlets.

atsOutletCtrlTableIndex.name: atsOutletCtrlTableIndex
atsOutletCtrlTableIndex.description: The index to the outlet entry.

atsOutletCtrlOutletName.name: atsOutletCtrlOutletName
atsOutletCtrlOutletName.description: The name of the outlet. The maximum string size is device dependent. An error will be returned if the set request exceeds the max size. This OID is provided for informational purposes only.

atsOutletCtrlCommand.name: atsOutletCtrlCommand
atsOutletCtrlCommand.description: Getting this variable will return the outlet state. If the outlet is on, the immediateOn (2) value will be returned. If the outlet is off, the immediateOff (2) value will be returned. Setting this variable to immediateOn (2) will immediately turn the outlet on. Setting this variable to immediateOff (3) will immediately turn the outlet off. Setting this variable to immediateReboot (4) will immediately reboot the outlet. Setting this variable to delayedOn (5) will turn the outlet on after the ePDUOutletConfigPowerOnTime OID time has elapsed. Setting this variable to delayedOff (6) will turn the outlet off after the ePDUOutletConfigPowerOffTime OID time has elapsed. Setting this variable to delayedReboot (7) will cause the ATS to perform a delayedOff command, wait the atsOutletCfgRebootDuration OID time, and then perform a delayedOn command. Setting this variable to cancelPendingCommand (8) will cause any pending command to this outlet to be canceled.

atsOutletCfgTableSize.name: atsOutletCfgTableSize
atsOutletCfgTableSize.description: The size of the outlet config table.

atsOutletCfgTable.name: atsOutletCfgTable
atsOutletCfgTable.description: Allows for configuration of individual outlets.

atsOutletCfgTableIndex.description: The index to the outlet entry.

atsOutletCfgOutletName.name: atsOutletCfgOutletName
atsOutletCfgOutletName.description: The name of the outlet. The maximum string size is device dependent. An error will be returned if the set request exceeds the max size.

atsOutletCfgPowerOnTime.name: atsOutletCfgPowerOnTime
atsOutletCfgPowerOnTime.description: The amount of time (in seconds) the outlet will delay powering on at coldstart or when a command that requires a turn-on delay is issued. Allowed values are: -1 - never power on. 0 - power on immediately. 1 to 7200 - power on up to 7200 seconds after being commanded.

atsOutletCfgPowerOffTime.name: atsOutletCfgPowerOffTime
atsOutletCfgPowerOffTime.description: The amount of time (in seconds) the outlet will delay powering off when a command that requires a turn-off delay is issued. Allowed values are: -1 - never power off. 0 - power off immediately. 1 to 7200 - power off up to 7200 seconds after being commanded.

atsOutletCfgRebootDuration.name: atsOutletCfgRebootDuration
atsOutletCfgRebootDuration.description: During a reboot sequence, power is turned off and then back on. This OID defines the amount of time to wait, in seconds, after turning the power off, at the start of the sequence, before turning power back on, at the end of the reboot sequence. Allowed range is any value between 5 and 60 seconds (1 minute).

ePDU2DeviceConfigDisplayOrientation.description: Getting this OID will return the intended physical orientation of the Seven-Segment Display. displayNormal(1) indicates Normal. displayReverse(2)indicates Upside-Down. displayRotate90(3) indicates rotate 90 degree. displayRotate270(4) indicates rotate 270 degree. displayAuto(5) indicates auto-detect and rotate.

ePDU2DeviceConfigColdstartDelay.description: The amount of delay, measured in seconds, between when power is provided to the Rack PDU and when the Rack PDU provides basic master power to the outlets. ePDU2DeviceConfigPeakLoadReset.description: Setting this OID to resetAll (2) will cause the existing peak current value of Rack PDU and its outlets to be replaced by the current load current value. Setting this OID to resetDevice (3) to reset the Rack PDU only. Setting this OID to resetOutlets (4) to reset the PDU outlets only. ePDU2DeviceInfoBreakerRating.description: The maximum current rating, measured in Amps, for the Rack PDU. Getting this OID will return rating of the circuit breakers on the device if it has any.

ePDU2DeviceInfoOutletLayout.name: ePDU2DeviceInfoOutletLayout
ePDU2DeviceInfoOutletLayout.description: Getting this OID will return outlet layout for the device. SeqPhaseToNeutral(1) indicates outlet layout as follows: 1:1-N,2:2-N,3:3-N,4:1-N,5:2-N,... SeqPhaseToPhase(2) indicates outlet layout as follows: 1:1-2,2:2-3,3:3-1,4:1-2,5:2-3,... SeqPhToNeu21PhToPh(3) indicates outlet layout as follows: 1:1-N,2:2-N...21:3-N,22:1-2,23:2-3,24:3-1,... SeqPhToPhGrouped(4) indicates outlet layout as follows: Otlts1-8::(3-1),Otlts9-16::(2-3),Otlts17-24::(1-2).

ePDU2DeviceControlCommand.name: ePDU2DeviceControlCommand
ePDU2DeviceControlCommand.description: Setting this OID to immediateAllOn (1) will turn all outlets on immediately. Setting this OID to immediateAllOff (2) will turn all outlets off immediately. Setting this OID to immediateAllReboot (3) will cause an immediateAllOff command to be performed. Once all outlets are off, the Switched Rack PDU will then delay the ePDU2OutletSwitchedConfigRebootDuration OID time, and then perform an immediateAllOn command. Setting this OID to delayedAllOn (4) will turn all outlets on as defined by each outlet's ePDU2OutletSwitchedConfigPowerOnTime OID value. Setting this OID to delayedAllOff (5) will turn all outlets off as defined by each outlet's ePDU2OutletSwitchedConfigPowerOffTime OID value. Setting this OID to delayedAllReboot (6) will cause a delayedAllOff command to be performed. Once all outlets are off, the Switched Rack PDU will then delay the largest ePDU2OutletSwitchedConfigRebootDuration OID time, and then perform a delayedAllOn command. Setting this OID to cancelAllPendingCommand (7) will cause all pending commands on the Switched Rack PDU to be cancelled. Setting this OID to noCommand (8) will have no effect. Getting this OID will return the noCommand (8) value.

ePDU2OutletSwitchedControlCommand.name: ePDU2OutletSwitchedControlCommand
ePDU2OutletSwitchedControlCommand.description: Getting this variable will return the outlet state. If the outlet is on, the immediateOn (1) value will be returned. If the outlet is off, the immediateOff (2) value will be returned. Setting this variable to immediateOn (1) will immediately turn the outlet on. Setting this variable to immediateOff (2) will immediately turn the outlet off. Setting this variable to immediateReboot (3) will immediately reboot the outlet. Setting this variable to delayedOn (4) will turn the outlet on after the ePDUOutletConfigPowerOnTime OID time has elapsed. Setting this variable to delayedOff (5) will turn the outlet off after the ePDUOutletConfigPowerOffTime OID time has elapsed. Setting this variable to delayedReboot (6) will cause the Switched Rack PDU to perform a delayedOff command, wait the ePDUOutletConfigRebootDuration OID time, and then perform a delayedOn command. Setting this variable to cancelPendingCommand (7) will cause any pending command to this outlet to be canceled. Setting this variable to outletIdentify (8) will cause PDU LED to display the number of the outlet.
